<div class="lang-en">
<section id="overview">
  <h2>What Is Qingming Festival?</h2>
  <p>Qingming (<span class="chinese-char">清明</span>, Qīngmíng) translates as "Clear Brightness" &mdash; a name that describes the quality of light in early April, when winter haze lifts and the sky turns sharp and luminous. It is the day the Chinese honour their dead: visiting graves, cleaning tombstones, burning offerings, and sharing a meal with ancestors who are no longer physically present but remain central to the family.</p>
  <p>Known in English as <strong>Tomb Sweeping Day</strong>, Qingming is one of the most important traditional Chinese festivals. Unlike the <a href="/spring-festival/">Spring Festival</a> (Chinese New Year), which is lunar, Qingming is a <strong>solar term</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">節氣</span>, jiéqì) &mdash; one of the 24 divisions of the <a href="/calendar/">Chinese solar calendar</a> that track the sun's position along the ecliptic. It falls each year between 4 and 6 April, when the sun reaches 15&deg; of celestial longitude.</p>
  <p>Qingming is simultaneously an act of filial piety (<span class="chinese-char">孝</span>, xiào), a seasonal marker for agriculture, and a celebration of spring's arrival. For more than 2,500 years, it has bound the living to the dead and the human world to the cycles of nature.</p>
</section>
</div>

<div class="lang-tc">
<section id="overview">
  <h2>什麼是清明節？</h2>
  <p>清明（<span class="chinese-char">清明</span>，Qīngmíng）意為「清潔明淨」——這個名稱描述了四月初的光線特質：冬日的霾霧散去，天空變得清澈明亮。這一天，華人緬懷先人：掃墓祭祖、清洗墓碑、焚燒祭品，與已不在人世但仍是家族核心的祖先共享一餐。</p>
  <p>清明節是最重要的中華傳統節日之一。與農曆為基礎的<a href="/spring-festival/">春節</a>不同，清明是一個<strong>節氣</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">節氣</span>，jiéqì）——<a href="/calendar/">中國陽曆</a>追蹤太陽在黃道上位置的二十四個劃分之一。每年當太陽到達黃經15度時即為清明，日期在4月4日至6日之間。</p>
  <p>清明同時是孝道（<span class="chinese-char">孝</span>，xiào）的體現、農業的季節標誌，以及迎春的慶典。兩千五百多年來，它將生者與逝者、人間與自然的輪迴緊密相連。</p>
</section>
</div>

