<section id="overview">
  <h2>什么是清明节？</h2>
  <p>清明（<span class="chinese-char">清明</span>，Qīngmíng）意为"清洁明净"——这个名称描述了四月初的光线特质：冬日的霾雾散去，天空变得清澈明亮。这一天，华人缅怀先人：扫墓祭祖、清洗墓碑、焚烧祭品，与已不在人世但仍是家族核心的祖先共享一餐。</p>
  <p>清明节是最重要的中华传统节日之一。与农历为基础的<a href="/spring-festival/">春节</a>不同，清明是一个<strong>节气</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">节气</span>，jiéqì）——<a href="/calendar/">中国阳历</a>追踪太阳在黄道上位置的二十四个划分之一。每年当太阳到达黄经15度时即为清明，日期在4月4日至6日之间。</p>
  <p>清明同时是孝道（<span class="chinese-char">孝</span>，xiào）的体现、农业的季节标志，以及迎春的庆典。两千五百多年来，它将生者与逝者、人间与自然的轮回紧密相连。</p>
</section>
</div>

<div class="lang-en">
<section id="history">
  <h2>History and Origins</h2>
  <p>Qingming's roots are ancient. The festival draws from at least three converging traditions:</p>
  <p><strong>1. The 24 Solar Terms.</strong> The solar term system was formalized during the Han Dynasty (206 BCE &ndash; 220 CE), though its origins reach further back. Qingming is the fifth solar term of spring, falling after the Spring Equinox (<span class="chinese-char">春分</span>) and before Grain Rain (<span class="chinese-char">穀雨</span>). The <em>Huainanzi</em> (<span class="chinese-char">淮南子</span>), a Western Han text, describes Qingming as the time when "the paulownia trees begin to flower" and "the mole crickets cry" &mdash; ecological signals that spring planting should begin.</p>
  <p><strong>2. The Cold Food Festival.</strong> The Cold Food Festival (<span class="chinese-char">寒食節</span>, Hánshí Jié), traditionally observed one or two days before Qingming, commemorates Jie Zitui (<span class="chinese-char">介子推</span>), a loyal minister of the state of Jin during the Spring and Autumn period (7th century BCE). After his lord Duke Wen of Jin came to power, Jie Zitui refused rewards and retreated to the mountains with his mother. When the duke ordered the mountain burned to force him out, Jie Zitui and his mother perished in the fire. In remorse, the duke ordered that no fires be lit on that day &mdash; hence the custom of eating only cold food. By the Tang Dynasty (618&ndash;907), the Cold Food Festival and Qingming had merged into a single observance.</p>
  <p><strong>3. Ancestral veneration.</strong> The practice of tending graves predates both the solar term system and the Jie Zitui legend. Oracle bone inscriptions from the Shang Dynasty (c. 1600&ndash;1046 BCE) record elaborate ancestor worship rituals. By the Zhou Dynasty (1046&ndash;256 BCE), regular grave maintenance and sacrificial offerings were codified in ritual texts such as the <em>Book of Rites</em> (<span class="chinese-char">禮記</span>, Lǐjì). Qingming became the primary occasion for this practice because spring &mdash; the season of renewal &mdash; was considered the ideal time to restore the resting places of the dead.</p>
  <p>The Tang poet Du Mu (<span class="chinese-char">杜牧</span>) captured the festival's atmosphere in what became its most famous poem: <em>"During Qingming, the rain falls without end / travellers on the road are weighed down with grief"</em> (<span class="chinese-char">清明時節雨紛紛，路上行人欲斷魂</span>). The poem is still recited today and remains one of the most widely known verses in the Chinese language.</p>
</section>
</div>

<div class="lang-tc">
<section id="history">
  <h2>歷史與起源</h2>
  <p>清明的歷史源遠流長，至少融合了三個傳統：</p>
  <p><strong>1. 二十四節氣。</strong>節氣體系在漢代（公元前206年至公元220年）正式確立，但其起源更為久遠。清明是春季的第五個節氣，在春分（<span class="chinese-char">春分</span>）之後、穀雨（<span class="chinese-char">穀雨</span>）之前。西漢典籍《淮南子》（<span class="chinese-char">淮南子</span>）記載清明時節「桐始華」「田鼠化為鴽」——這些物候信號標誌著春耕的開始。</p>
  <p><strong>2. 寒食節。</strong>寒食節（<span class="chinese-char">寒食節</span>，Hánshí Jié）傳統上在清明前一兩天，紀念春秋時期（公元前七世紀）晉國忠臣介子推（<span class="chinese-char">介子推</span>）。晉文公即位後，介子推拒絕封賞，攜母隱居山林。晉文公下令放火燒山逼其出山，介子推母子卻在大火中罹難。文公悔恨不已，下令當日禁火——由此有了只吃冷食的習俗。到唐代（618-907年），寒食節與清明節已合為一體。</p>
  <p><strong>3. 祖先崇拜。</strong>掃墓祭祖的習俗比節氣體系和介子推傳說更為古老。商代（約公元前1600-1046年）的甲骨文記錄了隆重的祖先祭祀儀式。到周代（公元前1046-256年），定期的墓地維護和祭祀活動已被編入《禮記》（<span class="chinese-char">禮記</span>，Lǐjì）等禮儀典籍。清明之所以成為祭祖的主要節日，是因為春天——萬物更新的季節——被認為是修繕先人安息之所的最佳時機。</p>
  <p>唐代詩人杜牧（<span class="chinese-char">杜牧</span>）以一首千古名詩描繪了清明的意境：<em>「清明時節雨紛紛，路上行人欲斷魂」</em>（<span class="chinese-char">清明時節雨紛紛，路上行人欲斷魂</span>）。這首詩至今仍被傳誦，是中國文學中最廣為人知的詩句之一。</p>
</section>
</div>

<div class="lang-sc">
<section id="history">
  <h2>历史与起源</h2>
  <p>清明的历史源远流长，至少融合了三个传统：</p>
  <p><strong>1. 二十四节气。</strong>节气体系在汉代（公元前206年至公元220年）正式确立，但其起源更为久远。清明是春季的第五个节气，在春分（<span class="chinese-char">春分</span>）之后、谷雨（<span class="chinese-char">穀雨</span>）之前。西汉典籍《淮南子》（<span class="chinese-char">淮南子</span>）记载清明时节"桐始华""田鼠化为鴽"——这些物候信号标志着春耕的开始。</p>
  <p><strong>2. 寒食节。</strong>寒食节（<span class="chinese-char">寒食節</span>，Hánshí Jié）传统上在清明前一两天，纪念春秋时期（公元前七世纪）晋国忠臣介子推（<span class="chinese-char">介子推</span>）。晋文公即位后，介子推拒绝封赏，携母隐居山林。晋文公下令放火烧山逼其出山，介子推母子却在大火中罹难。文公悔恨不已，下令当日禁火——由此有了只吃冷食的习俗。到唐代（618-907年），寒食节与清明节已合为一体。</p>
  <p><strong>3. 祖先崇拜。</strong>扫墓祭祖的习俗比节气体系和介子推传说更为古老。商代（约公元前1600-1046年）的甲骨文记录了隆重的祖先祭祀仪式。到周代（公元前1046-256年），定期的墓地维护和祭祀活动已被编入《礼记》（<span class="chinese-char">禮記</span>，Lǐjì）等礼仪典籍。清明之所以成为祭祖的主要节日，是因为春天——万物更新的季节——被认为是修缮先人安息之所的最佳时机。</p>
  <p>唐代诗人杜牧（<span class="chinese-char">杜牧</span>）以一首千古名诗描绘了清明的意境：<em>"清明时节雨纷纷，路上行人欲断魂"</em>（<span class="chinese-char">清明時節雨紛紛，路上行人欲斷魂</span>）。这首诗至今仍被传诵，是中国文学中最广为人知的诗句之一。</p>
</section>
</div>

<div class="lang-en">
<section id="2026-date">
  <h2>Qingming in 2026</h2>
  <p>In 2026, Qingming falls on <strong>Sunday, 5 April</strong>. In the context of the Chinese calendar, this marks the transition into the <strong>Chen (<span class="chinese-char">辰</span>) month</strong> &mdash; the Dragon month &mdash; which is the third month of the Chinese solar year.</p>
  <p>2026 is the year of <strong>Bǐngwǔ (<span class="chinese-char">丙午</span>)</strong>, the Fire Horse. The Qingming period in a Fire-dominant year carries particular significance: Fire is the element of illumination and transformation, and ancestor veneration is itself an act of keeping ancestral memory <em>bright</em> (<span class="chinese-char">明</span>, míng &mdash; the second character of Qingming). The alignment of Fire year energy with the festival's purpose is considered auspicious for meaningful connection with ancestors.</p>
  <p>In <a href="/bazi/">BaZi</a> analysis, the Qingming solar term is the precise boundary that separates the Mao (<span class="chinese-char">卯</span>, Rabbit) month from the Chen (<span class="chinese-char">辰</span>, Dragon) month. Anyone born on or after 5 April 2026 belongs to the Dragon month, while those born before that date belong to the Rabbit month &mdash; even if the calendar month is the same.</p>
</section>
</div>

<div class="lang-tc">
<section id="2026-date">
  <h2>2026年清明</h2>
  <p>2026年清明節在<strong>4月5日（星期日）</strong>。在中國曆法中，這一天標誌著進入<strong>辰（<span class="chinese-char">辰</span>）月</strong>——即龍月——中國陽曆的第三個月。</p>
  <p>2026年是<strong>丙午（<span class="chinese-char">丙午</span>）</strong>火馬年。火年的清明有特殊意義：火是光明與轉化的元素，而祭祖本身就是讓祖先的記憶保持<em>明亮</em>（<span class="chinese-char">明</span>，míng——清明的第二個字）的行為。火年能量與節日宗旨的契合，被認為有利於與祖先建立更有意義的連結。</p>
  <p>在<a href="/bazi/">八字</a>分析中，清明節氣是區分卯（<span class="chinese-char">卯</span>，兔）月和辰（<span class="chinese-char">辰</span>，龍）月的精確分界線。2026年4月5日當天或之後出生的人屬於龍月，而在此之前出生的人則屬於兔月——即使日曆月份相同。</p>
</section>
</div>

